Let a function g : [ 0, 4 ] $$\to$$ R be defined as 

$$g(x) = \left\{ {\matrix{
   {\mathop {\max }\limits_{0 \le t \le x} \{ {t^3} - 6{t^2} + 9t - 3),} & {0 \le x \le 3}  \cr 
   {4 - x,} & {3 < x \le 4}  \cr 

 } } \right.$$, then the number of points in the interval (0, 4) where g(x) is NOT differentiable, is ____________.

